  "prompt": "What is the meaning of Hanuman Chalisa?",
  "response": "Hanuman Chalisa is a Hindu devotional hymn dedicated to Lord Hanuman, a central figure in the epic Ramayana. The term \"Chalisa\" means \"forty\" in Hindi, referring to the 40 verses that compose this prayer. Here are key details about Hanuman Chalisa:\n\n1. Composition:\n- Written by Goswami Tulsidas in Hindi\n- Composed in the 16th century\n- Describes Hanuman's virtues, powers, and devotion to Lord Rama\n\n2. Main themes:\n- Praise of Hanuman's strength and courage\n- Narration of Hanuman's role in the Ramayana\n- Describes Hanuman as a symbol of devotion, loyalty, and divine power\n\n3. Significance:\n- Considered a powerful prayer for protection and overcoming obstacles\n- Believed to bring courage, strength, and spiritual blessings\n- Recited by devotees to seek Hanuman's divine intervention\n\n4. Purpose:\n- Worship and glorification of Lord Hanuman\n- Seeking spiritual guidance and protection\n- Expressing devotion and gratitude\n\nHanuman Chalisa is widely recited in temples, homes, and during religious ceremonies, and is an important part of Hindu devotional literature.",
